==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shadrach
<hw>Sha"drach</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Metal.)</fld>
<def>A mass of iron on which the operation of smelting has failed of its
intended effect; -- so called from <xex>Shadrach</xex>, one of the three
Hebrews who came forth unharmed from the fiery furnace of
Nebuchadnezzar. (See <au>Dan. iii. 26, 27.</au>)</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shad-spirit</ent>⟦br⟧
